==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English [[flod]], from Old English [[flod|flód]], from common Germanic ''*flōduz'', from Proto-Indo-European ''*plō-tu-'', derived from ''*pleu-'' "to flow". Near cognates include German [[Flut]] and Gothic [[𐍆𐌻𐍉𐌳𐌿𐍃]] (flōdus).  

===Pronunciation===
*flŭd, /flʌd/, /<tt>flVd</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ʌd|Rhymes: -ʌd]]

===Noun===
'''flood''' (''plural'' [[floods]])

#A (usually disastrous) overflow of [[water]] from a [[lake]] or other [[body of water]] due to excessive [[rainfall]] or other input of water.
#(''figuratively'') A large number or quantity of anything appearing more rapidly than can easily be dealt with.

